# PESSY — Cursor AI Rules

## CRITICAL: Never deploy hosting

DO NOT run `firebase deploy` or any firebase hosting command.
This WILL break pessy.app for 50,000+ users.

The only safe deploy command is: `bash deploy-with-landing.sh`
And it must be run from the `pessy-website` branch only.

## Branch rules

- `main` → development only, NEVER deploy from here
- `pessy-website` → production, deploy ONLY via `bash deploy-with-landing.sh`
- All other branches → never deploy

## Files never to modify without user approval

- `firebase.json` — hosting config is fragile, any change can break prod routing
- `src/auth/login/firebase.ts` — auth config, changes require full QA
- `public/landing.html` — production landing page
- `deploy-with-landing.sh` — deploy script

## Architecture

- `/` → `public/landing.html` (copied to `dist/index.html` at deploy time)
- `/login`, `/inicio`, `/register-*` → React SPA (`dist/app.html`)
- Stack: React 18 + TypeScript + Vite 6 + Tailwind v4 + Firebase

## Style

- Language: Argentine Spanish ("vos", informal)
- Primary color: #074738
- Font: Plus Jakarta Sans
- Border radius: 2rem
